47 equals negative 1\"><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>47</mn><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math> yields <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x equals 46\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>46</mn></math>. Therefore, the sum of the solutions to the given equation is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"48 plus 46\"><mn>48</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>46</mn></math>, or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"94\"><mn>94</mn></math>.</p>","externalid":"8204e6e4-4fd9-46f0-8199-646409cd8719","correct_answer":["94"]}}